quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  55,26,Everyone on it (the earth) is mortal
  55,27,"while your Master's essence, having the majesty and the nobility remains (forever)"
  55,28,Then which of your Master’s favors do you deny
  55,29,Everyone in the skies and on the earth ask Him (for their needs). Every day He is in some affair
  55,30,Then which of your Master’s favors do you deny
  55,31,"We are going to attend to you, the two important beings (humans and Jinn)"
  55,32,Then which of your Master’s favors do you deny
  55,33,"You, group of Jinn and humans, if you can cross the boundaries of the skies and the earth then cross. You cannot cross except with an authorization"
  55,34,Then which of your Master’s favors do you deny
  55,35,"A flame of fire and melted copper will be sent upon both of you, and you cannot help/defend yourselves"
  55,36,Then which of your Master’s favors do you deny
  55,37,And when the sky splits and it becomes red like the red rawhide (or red hot oil)
  55,38,Then which of your Master’s favors do you deny
  55,39,On that day no human being or Jinn is asked about his sin
  55,40,Then which of your Master’s favors do you deny
  55,41,"The guilty ones are recognized by their appearance, then they are taken by (the hair lock of) the forehead and the feet"
  55,42,Then which of your Master’s favors do you deny
  55,43,This is hell that the guilty ones deny it
  55,44,They go around between it and between hot boiling water
  55,45,Then which of your Master’s favors do you deny